scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/bofm/2-ne/9.html?verse=18#p18" href="/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/9.18?lang=eng#p18">2 Nephi 9:18</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/bofm/2-ne/31.html?verse=20#p20" href="/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/31.20?lang=eng#p20">31:20</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/dc-testament/dc/84.html?verse=38#p38" href="/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/84.38?lang=eng#p38">Doctrine and Covenants 84:38</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/dc-testament/dc/132.html?verse=49#p49" href="/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/132.49?lang=eng#p49">132:49</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/pgp/moses/1.html?verse=39#p39" href="/scriptures/pgp/moses/1.39?lang=eng#p39">Moses 1:39</a>.</p></li><li data-marker=12. id=note12><p data-aid=141537187 id=note12_p1>See <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/bofm/hel/12.html?verse=23#p23" href="/scriptures/bofm/hel/12.23?lang=eng#p23">Helaman 12:23</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/bofm/moro/10.html?verse=33#p33" href="/scriptures/bofm/moro/10.33?lang=eng#p33">Moroni 10:33</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/dc-testament/dc/58.html?verse=42#p42" href="/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/58.42?lang=eng#p42">Doctrine and Covenants 58:42</a>.</p></li><li data-marker=13. id=note13><p data-aid=141537196 id=note13_p1>See <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/bofm/alma/34.html?verse=33#p33" href="/scriptures/bofm/alma/34.33?lang=eng#p33">Alma 34:33</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/dc-testament/dc/82.html?verse=18#p18" href="/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/82.18?lang=eng#p18">Doctrine and Covenants 82:18</a>.</p></li><li data-marker=14. id=note14><p data-aid=141537204 id=note14_p1>See <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href=../../../scriptures/nt/heb/11.html href="/scriptures/nt/heb/11?lang=eng">Hebrews 11</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/bofm/2-ne/31.html?verse=19-20#p19" href="/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/31.19-20?lang=eng#p19">2 Nephi 31:19–20</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/bofm/alma/32.html?verse=21#p21" href="/scriptures/bofm/alma/32.21?lang=eng#p21">Alma 32:21</a>.</p></li><li data-marker=15. id=note15><p data-aid=141537205 id=note15_p1>See <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/ot/josh/24.html?verse=15#p15" href="/scriptures/ot/josh/24.15?lang=eng#p15">Joshua 24:15</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/dc-testament/dc/109.html?verse=8#p8" href="/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/109.8?lang=eng#p8">Doctrine and Covenants 109:8</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/dc-testament/dc/132.html?verse=19#p19" href="/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/132.19?lang=eng#p19">132:19</a>.</p></li><li data-marker=16. id=note16><p data-aid=141537217 id=note16_p1>See <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/ot/ex/19.html?verse=5#p5" href="/scriptures/ot/ex/19.5?lang=eng#p5">Exodus 19:5</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/bofm/1-ne/14.html?verse=14#p14" href="/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/14.14?lang=eng#p14">1 Nephi 14:14</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/bofm/2-ne/11.html?verse=5#p5" href="/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/11.5?lang=eng#p5">2 Nephi 11:5</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/dc-testament/dc/54.html?verse=6#p6" href="/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/54.6?lang=eng#p6">Doctrine and Covenants 54:6</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/dc-testament/dc/66.html?verse=2#p2" href="/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/66.2?lang=eng#p2">66:2</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/dc-testament/dc/90.html?verse=24#p24" href="/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/90.24?lang=eng#p24">90:24</a>.</p></li><li data-marker=17. id=note17><p data-aid=141537224 id=note17_p1>See <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/bofm/mosiah/13.html?verse=30#p30" href="/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/13.30?lang=eng#p30">Mosiah 13:30</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/bofm/alma/30.html?verse=3#p3" href="/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.3?lang=eng#p3">Alma 30:3</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/dc-testament/dc/84.html?verse=20-22#p20" href="/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/84.20-22?lang=eng#p20">Doctrine and Covenants 84:20–22</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/pgp/a-of-f/1.html?verse=3#p3" href="/scriptures/pgp/a-of-f/1.3?lang=eng#p3">Articles of Faith 1:3</a>.</p></li><li data-marker=18. id=note18><p data-aid=141537233 id=note18_p1>See <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/ot/ps/24.html?verse=3#p3" href="/scriptures/ot/ps/24.3?lang=eng#p3">Psalm 24:3</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/ot/isa/2.html?verse=3#p3" href="/scriptures/ot/isa/2.3?lang=eng#p3">Isaiah 2:3</a>; <a class=scripture-ref data-old-href="../../../scriptures/ot/ezek/37.html?verse=26#p26" href="/scriptures/ot/ezek/37.26?lang=eng#p26">Ezekiel 37:26</a>.</p></li><li data-marker=19. id=note19><p data-aid=141537239 id=note19_p1>Neal A. Maxwell, <cite>All These Things Shall Give Thee Experience</cite> (1979), 55.</p></li><li data-marker=20. id=note20><p data-aid=141537246 id=note20_p1>Classes should be referred to by the unifying title of “Young Women.” To identify a specific class, include the age﻿—for example, “Young Women 12–14”; “Young Women 15–18” (see <cite>Handbook 2: Administering the Church,</cite> <a class=cross-ref data-old-href="../../../manual/handbook-2-administering-the-church/young-women/young-women.html?para=title_number7#title_number7" href="/manual/handbook-2-administering-the-church/young-women/young-women?lang=eng&para=title_number7#title_number7">10.1.5</a>, ChurchofJesusChrist.org).</p></li><li data-marker=21. id=note21><p data-aid=141537251 id=note21_p1>A class presidency should be called for each Young Women class. Where possible, a full presidency should be called, with a president, two counselors, and a secretary. If needed, a partial presidency may be called (see <cite>Handbook 2,</cite> <a class=cross-ref data-old-href="../../../manual/handbook-2-administering-the-church/young-women/young-women.html?para=title_number14#title_number14" href="/manual/handbook-2-administering-the-church/young-women/young-women?lang=eng&para=title_number14#title_number14">10.3.5</a>).</p></li><li data-marker=22. id=note22><p data-aid=141537258 id=note22_p1>See <cite>Handbook 2,</cite> <a class=cross-ref data-old-href="../../../manual/handbook-2-administering-the-church/young-women/young-women.html?para=title_number14#title_number14" href="/manual/handbook-2-administering-the-church/young-women/young-women?lang=eng&para=title_number14#title_number14">10.3.5</a>.</p></li><li data-marker=23. id=note23><p data-aid=141537266 id=note23_p1>See Russell M. Nelson “<a class=cross-ref data-old-href=../../../broadcasts/worldwide-devotional-for-young-adults/2018/06/hope-of-israel.html href="/broadcasts/worldwide-devotional-for-young-adults/2018/06/hope-of-israel?lang=eng">Hope of Israel</a>” (worldwide youth devotional, June 3, 2018), HopeofIsrael.ChurchofJesusChrist.org.</p></li><li data-marker=24. id=note24><p data-aid=141537272 id=note24_p1>Additional instruction is available for adult Young Women leaders in <cite>Handbook 2,</cite> <a class=cross-ref data-old-href=../../../manual/handbook-2-administering-the-church/young-women/young-women.html href="/manual/handbook-2-administering-the-church/young-women/young-women?lang=eng">chapter 10</a>.</p></li><li data-marker=25. id=note25><p data-aid=141537277 id=note25_p1>Henry B. Eyring, “<a class=cross-ref data-old-href=../../../general-conference/2002/10/rise-to-your-call.html href="/general-conference/2002/10/rise-to-your-call?lang=eng">Rise to Your Call</a>,” <cite>Ensign</cite> or <cite>Liahona,</cite> Nov. 2002, 76.</p></li><li data-marker=26. id=note26><p data-aid=141537284 id=note26_p1>If you have only one class and one class presidency, the full presidency can participate in ward youth council with the Aaronic Priesthood quorum presidents so there is a balance of young women and young men (see <cite>Handbook 2,</cite> <a class=cross-ref data-old-href="../../../manual/handbook-2-administering-the-church/meetings-in-the-church/meetings-in-the-church.html?para=title_number12#title_number12" href="/manual/handbook-2-administering-the-church/meetings-in-the-church/meetings-in-the-church?lang=eng&para=title_number12#title_number12">18.2.9</a>).</p></li></ol></footer></div></article><div class=startHandle-2o_6p touch-action=none></div><div class=endHandle-wg4Dv touch-action=none></div></div></section></section><div class=mobileNav-1qobD><a class="mobileIcon-3ABLr mobilePrev-1Jf8d" href="/study/ensign/2019/11/32harkness?lang=eng"><button dir=ltr class="iconButton--V5Iv navButton-WGhZC"><span class=hiddenTitleText-2SahY></span><svg style=width:1.625rem;height:1.625rem viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns=http://www.w3.org/2000/svg role=presentation> <path fill=currentColor d="M4.438 10.856a.77.77 0 0 1 .097-.117l6.709-6.71a.755.755 0 0 1 1.065-.003.751.751 0 0 1-.005 1.064L6.6 10.795h11.647c.403 0 .744.335.744.75 0 .417-.333.75-.744.75H6.565l5.74 5.739a.755.755 0 0 1 .004 1.065.751.751 0 0 1-1.065-.005l-6.71-6.709a.757.757 0 0 1-.127-.169.755.755 0 0 1-.416-.671c0-.31.184-.574.447-.689z"> </path></svg></button></a><a class="mobileIcon-3ABLr mobileNext-1J33m" href="/study/ensign/2019/11/34eyring?lang=eng"><button style=transform:scale(-1) class="iconButton--V5Iv navButton-WGhZC"><span class=hiddenTitleText-2SahY></span><svg style=width:1.625rem;height:1.625rem viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns=http://www.w3.org/2000/svg role=presentation> <path fill=currentColor d="M4.438 10.856a.77.77 0 0 1 .097-.117l6.709-6.71a.755.755 0 0 1 1.065-.003.751.751 0 0 1-.005 1.064L6.6 10.795h11.647c.403 0 .744.335.744.75 0 .417-.333.75-.744.75H6.565l5.74 5.739a.755.755 0 0 1 .004 1.065.751.751 0 0 1-1.065-.005l-6.71-6.709a.757.757 0 0 1-.127-.169.755.755 0 0 1-.416-.671c0-.31.184-.574.447-.689z"> </path></svg></button></a></div></div><aside class="sidePanel-3uL9p relatedContentPanel-2wEUz"><div class="innerPanel-3gbqC innerPanel-32K4X open-vPftH"><header class="panelHeader-2k7Jd relatedContentAllHeader-ZlzXP"><span>Related Content</span><button class=iconButton--V5Iv><span class=hiddenTitleText-2SahY></span><svg style=width:1.625rem;height:1.625rem viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns=http://www.w3.org/2000/svg role=presentation> <path fill=currentColor d="M11.4 13.06l4.596 4.597a.749.749 0 1 0 1.06-1.06l-4.595-4.597 4.596-4.596a.749.749 0 1 0-1.06-1.06l-4.597 4.595-4.596-4.596a.749.749 0 1 0-1.06 1.06l4.595 4.597-4.596 4.596a.749.749 0 1 0 1.06 1.06l4.597-4.595z"> </path></svg></button></header><div class=panelContent-2dg-k><section class=panelGridLayout-3J74n style="-ms-grid-rows:auto (10px auto)[6]"><span style=-ms-grid-row:1>1.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:1><p data-aid=141537099 id=note1_p1>See <a class="" href="">Romans 8:35–39</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:3>2.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:3><p data-aid=141537107 id=note2_p1>Russell M. Nelson, “<a class="" href="">Witnesses, Aaronic Priesthood Quorums, and Young Women Classes</a>,” <cite>Ensign</cite> or <cite>Liahona,</cite> Nov. 2019, 39.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:5>3.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:5><p data-aid=141537114 id=note3_p1>See <a class="" href="">Proverbs 3:5–7</a>; <a class="" href="">Jacob 7:5</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:7>4.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:7><p data-aid=141537124 id=note4_p1>See <a class="" href="">Romans 8:16–17</a>; <a class="" href="">Doctrine and Covenants 76:24</a>; “<a class="" href="">The Family: A Proclamation to the World</a>,” <cite>Ensign</cite> or <cite>Liahona,</cite> May 2017, 145.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:9>5.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:9><p data-aid=141537132 id=note5_p1>See <a class="" href="">2 Peter 1:3–4</a>; <a class="" href="">Alma 37:44</a>; <a class="" href="">Doctrine and Covenants 78:18</a>; “<a class="" href="">The Family: A Proclamation to the World</a>.”</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:11>6.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:11><p data-aid=141537141 id=note6_p1>See <a class="" href="">John 13:14–15, 35</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:13>7.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:13><p data-aid=141537149 id=note7_p1>See <a class="" href="">Matthew 22:37–39</a>; <a class="" href="">25:40</a>; <a class="" href="">3 Nephi 12:48</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:15>8.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:15><p data-aid=141537157 id=note8_p1>See <a class="" href="">John 16:13</a>; <a class="" href="">3 Nephi 14:7–8</a>; <a class="" href="">Moroni 7:13</a>; <a class="" href="">10:5</a>; <a class="" href="">Doctrine and Covenants 8:2</a>; <a class="" href="">9:8</a>; <a class="" href="">11:13</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:17>9.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:17><p data-aid=141537165 id=note9_p1>See <a class="" href="">Matthew 20:26–28</a>; <a class="" href="">22:37–39</a>; <a class="" href="">25:34–40</a>; <a class="" href="">3 Nephi 26:19</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:19>10.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:19><p data-aid=141537173 id=note10_p1>See <a class="" href="">Isaiah 43:10</a>; <a class="" href="">Mosiah 18:9</a>; <a class="" href="">Doctrine and Covenants 14:8</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:21>11.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:21><p data-aid=141537182 id=note11_p1>See <a class="" href="">Romans 8:17</a>; <a class="" href="">2 Nephi 9:18</a>; <a class="" href="">31:20</a>; <a class="" href="">Doctrine and Covenants 84:38</a>; <a class="" href="">132:49</a>; <a class="" href="">Moses 1:39</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:23>12.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:23><p data-aid=141537187 id=note12_p1>See <a class="" href="">Helaman 12:23</a>; <a class="" href="">Moroni 10:33</a>; <a class="" href="">Doctrine and Covenants 58:42</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:25>13.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:25><p data-aid=141537196 id=note13_p1>See <a class="" href="">Alma 34:33</a>; <a class="" href="">Doctrine and Covenants 82:18</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:27>14.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:27><p data-aid=141537204 id=note14_p1>See <a class="" href="">Hebrews 11</a>; <a class="" href="">2 Nephi 31:19–20</a>; <a class="" href="">Alma 32:21</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:29>15.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:29><p data-aid=141537205 id=note15_p1>See <a class="" href="">Joshua 24:15</a>; <a class="" href="">Doctrine and Covenants 109:8</a>; <a class="" href="">132:19</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:31>16.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:31><p data-aid=141537217 id=note16_p1>See <a class="" href="">Exodus 19:5</a>; <a class="" href="">1 Nephi 14:14</a>; <a class="" href="">2 Nephi 11:5</a>; <a class="" href="">Doctrine and Covenants 54:6</a>; <a class="" href="">66:2</a>; <a class="" href="">90:24</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:33>17.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:33><p data-aid=141537224 id=note17_p1>See <a class="" href="">Mosiah 13:30</a>; <a class="" href="">Alma 30:3</a>; <a class="" href="">Doctrine and Covenants 84:20–22</a>; <a class="" href="">Articles of Faith 1:3</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:35>18.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:35><p data-aid=141537233 id=note18_p1>See <a class="" href="">Psalm 24:3</a>; <a class="" href="">Isaiah 2:3</a>; <a class="" href="">Ezekiel 37:26</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:37>19.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:37><p data-aid=141537239 id=note19_p1>Neal A. Maxwell, <cite>All These Things Shall Give Thee Experience</cite> (1979), 55.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:39>20.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:39><p data-aid=141537246 id=note20_p1>Classes should be referred to by the unifying title of “Young Women.” To identify a specific class, include the age﻿—for example, “Young Women 12–14”; “Young Women 15–18” (see <cite>Handbook 2: Administering the Church,</cite> <a class="" href="">10.1.5</a>, ChurchofJesusChrist.org).</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:41>21.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:41><p data-aid=141537251 id=note21_p1>A class presidency should be called for each Young Women class. Where possible, a full presidency should be called, with a president, two counselors, and a secretary. If needed, a partial presidency may be called (see <cite>Handbook 2,</cite> <a class="" href="">10.3.5</a>).</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:43>22.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:43><p data-aid=141537258 id=note22_p1>See <cite>Handbook 2,</cite> <a class="" href="">10.3.5</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:45>23.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:45><p data-aid=141537266 id=note23_p1>See Russell M. Nelson “<a class="" href="">Hope of Israel</a>” (worldwide youth devotional, June 3, 2018), HopeofIsrael.ChurchofJesusChrist.org.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:47>24.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:47><p data-aid=141537272 id=note24_p1>Additional instruction is available for adult Young Women leaders in <cite>Handbook 2,</cite> <a class="" href="">chapter 10</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:49>25.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:49><p data-aid=141537277 id=note25_p1>Henry B. Eyring, “<a class="" href="">Rise to Your Call</a>,” <cite>Ensign</cite> or <cite>Liahona,</cite> Nov. 2002, 76.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:51>26.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:51><p data-aid=141537284 id=note26_p1>If you have only one class and one class presidency, the full presidency can participate in ward youth council with the Aaronic Priesthood quorum presidents so there is a balance of young women and young men (see <cite>Handbook 2,</cite> <a class="" href="">18.2.9</a>).</p></div></section></div></div></aside></div></main><div><div><script type=text/javascript> var channel = 'www.lds.org'; var pageName = 'www.lds.org:""'; var 